+╭────────────────────────────────── 📋 Specification (spec.md) ───────────────────────────────────╮│ # banking-app                                                                                   ││                                                                                                 ││ ## Initial Description                                                                          ││ "An app that allows a number of operations, including withdrawal, deposits, and transfers -     ││ establishing identity of the user using a password"                                             ││                                                                                                 ││ ## System Architecture Overview                                                                 ││                                                                                                 ││ ### Core Architecture                                                                           ││ - **Single process server** with request queue processing                                       ││ - **JSON-based persistence** in `.db` directory structure                                       ││ - **Pydantic data models** for validation and serialization                                     ││ - **In-memory locking** for concurrency control                                                 ││                                                                                                 ││ ### System Hierarchy                                                                            ││ ```                                                                                             ││ Banking App                                                                                     ││ ├── Authentication System                                                                       ││ ├── Data Models & Persistence                                                                   ││ ├── Banking Operations                                                                          ││ └── Concurrency & Security                                                                      ││ ```                                                                                             ││                                                                                                 ││ ## Authentication System                                                                        ││                                                                                                 ││ ### Password Management                                                                         ││ - User passwords are stored as hashes in an identity file                                       ││ - Password verification occurs by comparing against stored hashes                               ││ - Identity file serves as persistent storage for user credentials                               ││ - **No password complexity requirements** - users may choose any password they prefer           ││                                                                                                 ││ ### Session Management                                                                          ││ - Upon successful password verification, a session key is generated                             ││ - Session key is created as hash(user identity + salt)                                          ││ - The system maintains a hash of the session key for verification                               ││ - **Session keys remain valid for 5 minutes**                                                   ││ - Session configuration managed through Pydantic class objects that are serialized              ││ - Global session parameters stored as Pydantic configuration objects                            ││                                                                                                 ││ ### Security Policies                                                                           ││                                                                                                 ││ #### Failed Login Attempts                                                                      ││ - Maximum of 3 failed login attempts allowed per user account                                   ││ - After 3 failed attempts, the user account is locked                                           ││ - Locked users must call the bank to unlock their account                                       ││ - Bank contact number: 1-800-BANK-HELP (placeholder - to be updated with actual contact         ││ information)                                                                                    ││                                                                                                 ││ ## Data Models & Persistence                                                                    ││                                                                                                 ││ ### Storage Architecture                                                                        ││ - All persistent data is stored as JSON files in a `.db` directory                              ││ - JSON format provides structured, human-readable persistence                                   ││ - Consistent storage approach across all application data                                       ││ - Pydantic models handle data validation and serialization before persistence                   ││                                                                                                 ││ ##                                                                                              ││                                                                                                 ││ ... (truncated - use editor to see full content)                                                │╰─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╯

