# 2025-12-05 09:14:36.159614
+This is not correct. When we have a component object we have the names of its pre and post conditions - these are saved in the json. We must validate this is true when saving. We will do an edit loop with the LLM (3 times) to make sure it is true when we are ready to do this. We will *always* adorn the function with @contract @precondition and @postcondition if they exist using the existing decorators. We will not write special decorators per implementation. Fix the implementation to use the standard decorators only and use the names of the logical operators for these in the logical file. 

