# 2025-12-06 23:51:30.932595
+/ask Ok, we want to create a langgraph agent which has several modes. One is planning mode in which we interactively chat about a specification. The specification we try to hone so that it can be turned into pre-contract and post-contract (verbal descriptions of pre and post conditions as well as invariant-contract which gives invariants. After we have completed this we go to precondition and postcondition writing mode. This will actually implement the pre and post conditions as boolean functions in a fragment of python which *cannot* use observable side effects (we will use a linter later to test). Next we have sketch mode. Here it will write out each taks or use conditionals to make branches but will just write out the major work as comments witha pass statement. If something looks like it might be substantial code it should write down a COMPONENT CANDIDATE note. Once we have completed the specification we will change to implementation mode. Here the LLM is instructed to produce a patch that will implement the specification - it can add which-ever helper functions it needs in this phase but it should not alter the contracts at all. We will do post filtering of patches to make sure this works.

# 2025-12-06 23:56:56.836190
+Please write a contract and stub for the agent. We are going to pretend that you are this agent while we are writing it. You will be in either 1, 2, 3 or 4. Currently we are in 1. Our agent should be an interactive CLI that allows me to edit my python code interactively. It should have access to files in the current git repo we invoke it from. It should commit after it has successfully run. 

